WEBVTT

00:01.335 --> 00:02.668
Sorry for the bumps.

00:02.669 --> 00:04.002
Traffic's backed up
for 20 miles.

00:04.005 --> 00:06.739
This is the only way
to the accident site.

00:06.741 --> 00:08.574
There should be a few medics
and emts,

00:08.576 --> 00:10.476
but we may be the only doctors
on site.

00:10.478 --> 00:12.328
Keep your heads on.

00:12.329 --> 00:14.179
There's gonna be a lot of people
there who need your help.

00:14.181 --> 00:17.516
This is<i> not</i> first come,
first served.

00:17.518 --> 00:21.553
Your primary job on initial eval
is to prioritize the patient.

00:21.555 --> 00:24.023
Each of you
take a packet of tags.

00:24.025 --> 00:25.457
There are four colors.

00:25.459 --> 00:27.459
Green is for minor injuries,

00:27.461 --> 00:29.461
yellow is for more
serious injuries,

00:29.463 --> 00:31.497
but not immediately
life-threatening.

00:31.499 --> 00:33.399
Red is for critical patients

00:33.401 --> 00:36.468
who won't survive without
treatment and transport.

00:36.470 --> 00:40.105
The black tag is for death
or expected death.

00:40.107 --> 00:41.807
Wait, "expected death"?

00:41.809 --> 00:44.443
Are you saying we put a black
tag on a living patient?

00:44.445 --> 00:46.278
You want us to decide
who lives and dies?

00:46.280 --> 00:49.448
We want you to decide
whose life you<i> can</i> save.

00:49.450 --> 00:52.618
And prevent the next doctor
or EMT who comes along

00:52.620 --> 00:55.587
from spending precious time
on an unsalvageable patient.

00:55.589 --> 00:57.790
There's nothing in your training
that's prepared you for this.

00:57.792 --> 01:00.592
Do it right and you'll save more
lives than you lose.

01:00.594 --> 01:02.561
Driver: We're here.

01:04.632 --> 01:08.300
[ Radio chatter ]

01:13.507 --> 01:15.607
[ Woman crying ]

01:15.609 --> 01:18.377
[ Siren wails ]

01:20.448 --> 01:23.849
[ Indistinct conversations ]

01:26.587 --> 01:28.654
That back there.

01:28.656 --> 01:32.357
All right,
let's unload our gear.

01:32.359 --> 01:34.526
Hello, folks.
Welcome to the zone.

01:34.528 --> 01:37.396
Sorry, who are you?

01:37.398 --> 01:38.797
D.I.C., doctor in charge.

01:38.799 --> 01:40.666
I'm the guy they send out
to all these train wrecks.

01:40.668 --> 01:42.201
Car wrecks. Whatever.

01:42.203 --> 01:44.203
I just got off the phone
with a Gina perello.

01:44.205 --> 01:46.238
She said I have two attendings,
four E.R. rez,

01:46.240 --> 01:48.173
and one surgical rez...
Who's the surgical?

01:48.175 --> 01:49.475
Heather pinkney.
I'm a surgeon, as well.

01:49.477 --> 01:50.876
We usually keep one in the tent,
one in the field.

01:50.878 --> 01:52.644
You're gonna be the roamer.

01:52.646 --> 01:54.713
You must be Dr. Rorish.
You're gonna be here with me.

01:54.715 --> 01:56.065
I'm better in the field.

01:56.066 --> 01:57.416
You're now in my E.R.,
Dr. Rorish.

01:57.418 --> 01:59.485
If I say you're in the tent,
you're in the tent.

01:59.487 --> 02:01.320
I need all this blood
organized by type.

02:01.322 --> 02:03.622
The rest of you, bags and tags.

02:03.624 --> 02:05.324
Let's move, folks.

02:05.326 --> 02:06.859
Oxygen tanks upright!
You good, leanne?

02:06.861 --> 02:09.728
Yeah. You go ahead.
Keep your wits about you.

02:09.730 --> 02:10.896
Good luck.
All right?

02:10.898 --> 02:12.631
See you on the other side.

02:12.633 --> 02:14.667
That guy's vest
is missing a "k."

02:14.668 --> 02:16.702
Where are the gurneys that
I asked for to be lined up here?

02:16.704 --> 02:19.771
Dr. Larson, over here.
I've got the driver.

02:19.773 --> 02:22.674
We're doctors.
I got the passenger.

02:22.676 --> 02:24.643
Help us! Please!

02:24.645 --> 02:26.612
Please, help us!

02:26.614 --> 02:28.180
It's okay.
We got you.
My arms are broken.

02:28.182 --> 02:29.682
Can you hear me?

02:29.683 --> 02:31.183
His head...
His head hit the window hard.

02:31.185 --> 02:32.618
His breathing is labored.
He's non-responsive...

02:32.620 --> 02:33.886
Are you a doctor?

02:33.888 --> 02:35.721
I'm a hospice nurse.
Alice sellers.

02:35.723 --> 02:37.789
How is he?
Is he your husband, Alice?

02:37.791 --> 02:39.241
Please, help him.
No, his name is Fred.

02:39.242 --> 02:40.692
His name is Fred.
We were at dinner.

02:40.694 --> 02:41.760
Okay. Okay.

02:41.762 --> 02:42.794
He's my date.

02:42.796 --> 02:44.596
Alice.
Yeah.

02:44.598 --> 02:45.797
I need to examine you.
Uh-huh.

02:45.799 --> 02:48.250
Do you have any other injuries?

02:48.251 --> 02:50.702
[ Groans ] My right arm.
My right foot is broken.

02:50.704 --> 02:52.571
Ow. Ow.

02:52.573 --> 02:56.642
Multiple fractures.
Suspect intraperitoneal bleed.

02:56.644 --> 02:59.478
Ow!
Hemorrhagic shock.

02:59.480 --> 03:00.679
Is... is he okay?

03:00.681 --> 03:02.748
I'm so sorry, Alice.

03:02.750 --> 03:03.815
Wha...
I'm so sorry.

03:03.817 --> 03:05.450
What? What? No!

03:05.452 --> 03:07.219
Let's get this lady back
to triage, please!

03:07.221 --> 03:08.687
I know what a black tag is.

03:08.689 --> 03:10.422
No, don't black-tag him.

03:10.424 --> 03:12.524
Okay. Okay.
He's still breathing!

03:12.526 --> 03:14.693
He's still breathing!

03:14.695 --> 03:16.228
Man:
<i>Police and fire rescue teams</i>

03:16.230 --> 03:18.230
<i>are hindered in getting
to the accident site</i>

03:18.232 --> 03:20.632
<i>by the heavy fog and the
traffic gridlock all around it.</i>

03:20.634 --> 03:21.767
Are my people on site yet?

03:21.769 --> 03:22.868
Just arrived.

03:22.870 --> 03:24.636
Man:
Angels base, 911 dispatch.

03:24.638 --> 03:25.804
I have a call from the scene.

03:25.806 --> 03:27.406
Sounds like a kid.
I'm gonna transfer her.

03:27.408 --> 03:29.308
Uh, no, no.
That... that goes to 911.

03:29.310 --> 03:30.809
We only talk to medics.

03:30.811 --> 03:31.910
She sounds isolated.

03:31.912 --> 03:33.946
Can't quite make out
what she's saying.

03:33.948 --> 03:35.547
Says her mom's in bad shape.

03:35.549 --> 03:37.482
You start talking
to patients directly

03:37.484 --> 03:39.818
and you're going down
a rabbit hole... trust me.

03:39.820 --> 03:42.654
Girl: Hello?

03:42.656 --> 03:44.590
Is anybody there?

03:47.728 --> 03:49.962
Uh... Hello.

03:49.964 --> 03:52.931
This is Dr. perello
at angels memorial hospital.

03:52.933 --> 03:53.865
What's your name?

03:53.867 --> 03:55.000
[ Switch clicks ]
Lily.

03:55.002 --> 03:57.302
My mom and my brother
are back...

03:57.304 --> 03:58.770
[ Static ]

03:58.772 --> 04:02.374
And we... the car swerved
and we went over the...

04:02.376 --> 04:04.810
Lily, I'm having trouble
hearing you, sweetheart.

04:04.812 --> 04:07.746
We have doctors there.
They're wearing yellow vests.

04:07.748 --> 04:11.483
It's cold and...
I can't see anything.

04:11.485 --> 04:13.919
All right.
Lily, where are you, honey?

04:13.921 --> 04:15.854
[ Static ]

04:15.856 --> 04:16.822
Lily.

04:16.824 --> 04:18.624
[ Switch clicks ]

04:22.563 --> 04:24.529
Hello?

04:24.531 --> 04:26.832
Hello?

04:26.834 --> 04:28.867
Can you still hear me?

04:35.843 --> 04:38.677
[ Man shouts indistinctly ]

04:38.679 --> 04:40.712
[ Police radio chatter ]

04:40.714 --> 04:42.848
¶¶

04:42.850 --> 04:44.449
[ siren wails ]

04:56.797 --> 04:58.063
Look at that fog.
Can't see 10 feet.

04:58.065 --> 04:59.832
<i>Heavy fog conditions...</i>

04:59.833 --> 05:01.600
When it lifts and they start
bringing people back here,

05:01.602 --> 05:03.769
all hell's gonna break
loose downstairs.

05:03.771 --> 05:04.903
Be ready.

05:04.905 --> 05:07.839
<i>Now, so far, we only have...</i>

05:07.841 --> 05:10.409
You know, Jesse,
the nurses have been talking.

05:10.411 --> 05:13.712
They said that your, uh... your
discharge has been approved.

05:13.714 --> 05:16.014
Your labs are all back.
They're normal.

05:16.016 --> 05:19.918
Even if that was true,
that's private information.

05:19.920 --> 05:22.454
Those nurses shouldn't be
flapping their traps.

05:22.456 --> 05:24.022
Is it hot in here?

05:24.024 --> 05:25.924
No. No, and calm down.

05:25.926 --> 05:27.459
Look, it's just because
we miss you.

05:27.461 --> 05:28.960
[ Chuckles ]

05:28.962 --> 05:30.662
Ah, I did a lap.

05:30.664 --> 05:33.031
Feel like I just built
the pyramids. [ Chuckles ]
[ Groans ]

05:33.033 --> 05:34.399
Oh.

05:34.401 --> 05:36.768
Hi.
[ Door closes ]

05:36.770 --> 05:40.105
Amy, my roommate, Jack rhodes.

05:40.107 --> 05:41.039
Hello.

05:41.041 --> 05:43.008
Amy and I, we work together.

05:43.010 --> 05:44.543
Work friends, huh?

05:44.545 --> 05:47.779
Well, then I wish I was
a little better dressed

05:47.781 --> 05:49.348
for our first date.

05:49.350 --> 05:50.415
You would've totally scored.

05:50.417 --> 05:52.084
Oh, I like<i> her.</i>

05:52.086 --> 05:53.819
[ Monitor beeping ]

05:53.821 --> 05:55.654
Jesse, you okay, man?

05:55.656 --> 05:57.489
My chest is feeling
a little tight.

05:57.491 --> 05:59.558
Jesse.
Should we call a doctor?

05:59.560 --> 06:01.927
Talk to me.
Are you having any pain?

06:01.929 --> 06:04.062
I'm feeling nauseated and dizzy.

06:04.064 --> 06:06.698
Just try... try to slow down
your breathing, okay?

06:06.700 --> 06:07.699
I think you're hyperventilating.

06:07.701 --> 06:09.034
This can't be happening again.

06:09.036 --> 06:10.369
It's not.

06:10.371 --> 06:11.903
I want you to breathe with me,
all right?

06:11.905 --> 06:13.071
Okay. Okay.

06:13.073 --> 06:14.740
Four slow beats in
[Breathes deeply]

06:14.742 --> 06:17.476
Four slow beats out.
Good.

06:17.478 --> 06:19.411
Look at me.
You see me?

06:19.413 --> 06:21.947
You're okay.
It's not a heart attack.

06:21.949 --> 06:23.815
It's a panic attack.

06:23.817 --> 06:24.916
Okay.

06:24.918 --> 06:25.984
[ Breathes deeply ]
Keep breathing.

06:25.986 --> 06:28.887
Okay. Okay.

06:28.889 --> 06:30.155
Man: Over here.
Bring her over here.

06:30.157 --> 06:32.824
Abdomen is tense.
Cap refill delayed.

06:32.826 --> 06:34.993
[ Crying ] Please go back!

06:34.995 --> 06:36.862
BP is 60 over 40.

06:36.864 --> 06:38.530
I need a portable ultrasound,
please.

06:38.532 --> 06:39.865
He was breathing.

06:39.867 --> 06:41.666
His pupils
were non-responsive.

06:41.668 --> 06:43.068
Alice is a hospice nurse.

06:43.070 --> 06:45.454
My aunt was a hospice nurse.

06:45.455 --> 06:47.839
And my mother used to always say
she had one hand in heaven.

06:47.841 --> 06:50.409
All right. We've got free fluid
in the abdomen.

06:50.411 --> 06:53.011
Central line and fluids should
stabilize for transport.

06:53.013 --> 06:55.981
[ Sobbing ] He was alive.
They black-tagged him!

06:55.983 --> 06:58.016
They killed him!
You killed him!

06:58.018 --> 07:00.919
Dr. Lorenson,
it's time for you to go.

07:00.921 --> 07:02.454
You okay?
Yeah.

07:02.456 --> 07:04.055
It's not easy.

07:04.057 --> 07:05.123
[ Alice crying ]

07:05.125 --> 07:07.959
All right.
Just breathe.

07:07.961 --> 07:09.961
Okay. Come right this way.
Go to the orange tent.

07:09.963 --> 07:11.563
You're gonna be okay.

07:11.565 --> 07:13.432
[ Car horn honks ]

07:17.704 --> 07:19.638
What the hell?

07:24.878 --> 07:28.180
[ Siren wails ]

07:29.716 --> 07:31.483
Is anybody in there?

07:32.786 --> 07:35.654
Oh, my God.

07:38.625 --> 07:41.126
Aah! Aah!
Get me out of here!

07:41.128 --> 07:42.895
Help me!
Okay. Okay.

07:42.896 --> 07:44.663
Help me! Get me out of here!
I can't... I can't breathe!

07:44.665 --> 07:46.498
Okay. Okay. Okay.
What's your name?

07:46.500 --> 07:48.500
Kenny wylar. Get me out of here.
Please get me out of here!

07:48.502 --> 07:50.535
Kenny, I'm Dr. Leighton,
and I'm gonna help you, okay?

07:50.537 --> 07:52.204
Are y-you alone in here?

07:52.206 --> 07:53.705
It's just... Me and olaf.

07:53.707 --> 07:55.440
A doll for my daughter.

07:55.441 --> 07:57.174
She's gonna get upset if I can't
get him back to her.
Okay, okay.

07:57.177 --> 07:59.077
Kenny... Kenny,
she's gonna be more upset

07:59.079 --> 08:00.479
if we don't get <i>you</i> back, okay?

08:00.481 --> 08:01.546
Let's start with that.

08:01.548 --> 08:02.747
[ Groans ]
I can't breathe.

08:02.749 --> 08:04.049
Stay with me.
Stay with me.
Okay.

08:04.051 --> 08:05.250
Mario!
Heather!

08:05.252 --> 08:07.052
[ Groans ]

08:12.125 --> 08:14.526
[ Cellphone ringing ]

08:14.528 --> 08:15.528
[ Cellphone beeps ]

08:15.529 --> 08:17.246
Gina: Hi. It's Gina.

08:17.247 --> 08:18.964
A little girl called in before.
Her name is Lily.

08:18.966 --> 08:21.099
Sounded like her family
was in pretty bad shape.

08:21.101 --> 08:23.235
There's a lot of that out here,
unfortunately.

08:23.237 --> 08:25.136
I told her I'd send help.

08:25.138 --> 08:28.273
She's in an s.U.V.
She said it went over.

08:28.275 --> 08:30.876
Went over?
Went over what?

08:30.878 --> 08:33.044
I don't know.
That's all I could make out.

08:33.046 --> 08:34.246
Listen, if you find her...

08:34.248 --> 08:35.981
Yeah, okay.
I'll look for her.
Okay.

08:35.983 --> 08:37.015
Just let me know, all right?

08:37.017 --> 08:38.149
She sounded pretty freaked out.

08:38.151 --> 08:41.086
I'm not surprised.

08:41.088 --> 08:42.821
It's pretty freaky out here.

08:43.857 --> 08:45.207
[ Door rattles ]

08:45.208 --> 08:46.558
I can't breathe.
Mario: What the hell's this?

08:46.560 --> 08:47.560
Angus: It's jammed.

08:50.564 --> 08:51.597
Can't breathe.

08:51.598 --> 08:52.631
Okay, we need a crow bar
or an ax or something.

08:52.633 --> 08:54.165
Think we can dig him out?
Sure.

08:54.167 --> 08:55.834
If we had five hours, maybe.

08:55.836 --> 08:58.537
Doc, I-I'm freezing.
I-i can't feel my legs.

08:58.539 --> 08:59.271
[ Kenny groans ]

08:59.273 --> 09:01.273
Person: Somebody help!

09:01.275 --> 09:02.974
[ Truck horn blares ]

09:02.976 --> 09:04.309
Help me, please.

09:04.311 --> 09:05.310
All right, Kenny... Kenny,
we're gonna be right back.

09:05.312 --> 09:06.628
Stay with me, Kenny.

09:06.629 --> 09:07.945
We got no choice.
We got to black-tag him.

09:07.948 --> 09:09.247
Wait, what?!
Wow, what a hero.

09:09.249 --> 09:10.982
This is the job, okay?

09:10.983 --> 09:12.716
Prioritize based on who we can
reasonably save.

09:12.719 --> 09:14.019
We can save him.

09:14.021 --> 09:15.988
No, we can't.

09:15.989 --> 09:17.956
That concrete is cold, wet,
and is expanding as it dries.

09:17.958 --> 09:19.691
So he either asphyxiates
or he freezes to death.

09:19.693 --> 09:21.693
Either way, we're not gonna get
him out of there in time.

09:21.695 --> 09:23.228
You have a black heart.
I don't have
a black heart, okay?

09:23.230 --> 09:24.896
Mario, he's talking
and conscious.

09:24.898 --> 09:26.798
He's not a black tag.

09:26.799 --> 09:28.699
Thank you, Heather.
Then what are we
gonna do, huh?

09:28.702 --> 09:29.790
We fight the hypothermia.

09:29.791 --> 09:30.879
You go back
to that fire truck...

09:30.880 --> 09:31.968
It's about a half a mile back...
And get an ax.

09:31.972 --> 09:33.055
Hi, Kenny.

09:33.056 --> 09:34.139
Yeah, and how are you gonna
fight the hypothermia?

09:34.141 --> 09:35.240
We'll figure it out.

09:35.242 --> 09:37.242
Run, forrest, run!

09:37.244 --> 09:39.010
Okay. How are we gonna
keep him warm?

09:39.012 --> 09:40.462
It's not like we can put
a sun blanket around him.

09:40.463 --> 09:41.913
Not<i> around</i> him,<i> in</i> him.
Open that bag.

09:41.915 --> 09:43.114
I've got saline.

09:43.116 --> 09:44.666
We need warm saline,
and lots of it.

09:44.667 --> 09:46.217
Yeah, well, where are we
gonna get warm saline out here?

09:46.219 --> 09:48.620
Uh, we need a car that works.

09:48.622 --> 09:49.621
You think you're driving
somewhere?

09:49.623 --> 09:50.989
No, we're not driving.

09:50.991 --> 09:52.991
Bingo.

09:52.993 --> 09:54.159
Okay, Kenny?
Yeah?

09:54.161 --> 09:55.293
Kenny, we'll be
right back, okay?
No!

09:55.295 --> 09:56.361
Heather, let's go.

09:56.363 --> 09:59.664
[ Car beeping softly ]

10:02.636 --> 10:04.836
[ Siren wails ]

10:04.838 --> 10:06.605
Child: Help.

10:06.607 --> 10:09.274
Is anyone there?

10:11.612 --> 10:12.777
Can you help me?

10:14.915 --> 10:17.616
Hey. Hey.
Hey, it's okay.

10:17.618 --> 10:19.618
It's okay. I'm a doctor.
I'm gonna help you, okay?

10:19.620 --> 10:20.819
My mom...

10:20.821 --> 10:21.786
She's trapped.

10:21.788 --> 10:23.355
Whoa. Okay.

10:23.357 --> 10:24.689
Okay.

10:27.728 --> 10:29.694
[ Man shouts indistinctly ]

10:32.799 --> 10:35.000
Angus: Kenny...
Here.

10:35.002 --> 10:37.402
We're gonna run this I.V.
Wide open into your veins

10:37.404 --> 10:39.204
to keep you as warm as possible

10:39.206 --> 10:41.172
until we can figure
something out, okay?

10:41.174 --> 10:42.641
You're not gonna get me
out of here, are you?

10:42.643 --> 10:44.342
Yes, we are.
[ Groans ]

10:44.344 --> 10:46.044
I want to talk to my family.

10:46.046 --> 10:47.345
Do you have a phone?
Yeah.

10:47.347 --> 10:50.281
Uh, I need a volunteer
to hold this I.V.

10:50.283 --> 10:51.383
Here.
Where are you going?

10:51.385 --> 10:53.084
We need to go treat more people.

10:53.086 --> 10:55.186
This saline bag takes
12 minutes to empty.

10:55.188 --> 10:57.188
We'll be back by then, okay?

10:57.189 --> 10:59.189
Kenny. Kenny, look at me.
Do not give up.

10:59.192 --> 11:00.692
Keep moving in there, okay?

11:00.694 --> 11:02.694
Okay.

11:02.696 --> 11:04.062
Meet you back here in 12?

11:04.064 --> 11:05.797
You got it.
Thanks.

11:05.799 --> 11:07.332
8 years old.

11:07.334 --> 11:09.234
Disoriented and short of breath.

11:09.236 --> 11:10.969
Lost consciousness,
but coming out of it.

11:10.971 --> 11:13.071
Ribs could be fractured.
Possible internal bleed.

11:13.073 --> 11:14.873
I'm Dr. Rorish.
What's your name?

11:14.875 --> 11:16.341
Jason.

11:16.343 --> 11:18.243
My mom...
You have to help her.

11:18.245 --> 11:20.278
Jason says his mom's trapped
in the car somewhere.

11:20.280 --> 11:21.980
I told her I'd get help.

11:22.783 --> 11:25.250
I got lost.
Two broken ribs.

11:25.252 --> 11:28.086
One possibly punctured
the right lung.
[ Siren wails ]

11:28.088 --> 11:30.088
Jason, we're gonna have to
get you back to the hospital

11:30.090 --> 11:30.755
so that we can help you.

11:30.757 --> 11:31.956
No!
Shh.

11:31.958 --> 11:33.158
I'm not leaving without my mom!

11:33.160 --> 11:34.693
You've got to find her!

11:34.695 --> 11:36.195
We have one more for that bus,
please!

11:36.196 --> 11:37.696
I'm not leaving!
You've got to find her!

11:37.698 --> 11:38.430
This rig is shipping out<i> now.</i>

11:38.432 --> 11:40.198
Just wait!

11:40.199 --> 11:41.965
Jason, if your mom
were here, she'd want
you on that ambulance.

11:41.968 --> 11:44.235
I'm not leaving without her!
Let me up!

11:44.237 --> 11:46.738
Hey. Jason, what does
your mom's car look like?

11:46.740 --> 11:47.772
Hmm?

11:47.774 --> 11:50.241
Silver dodge.
Mm-hmm.

11:50.243 --> 11:52.477
It has a bumper sticker...
Mm-hmm.

11:52.479 --> 11:56.981
That says "my dog's not fat,
it's a husky."

11:56.983 --> 11:58.717
[ Chuckling ] Okay, good.

11:58.719 --> 11:59.718
You are going to that hospital.

11:59.720 --> 12:01.419
And we are gonna find your mom.

12:01.421 --> 12:03.221
What's her name?

12:03.223 --> 12:05.223
Connie.
Connie.

12:05.225 --> 12:06.891
You promise
you're gonna find her?

12:06.893 --> 12:08.727
Man: Ready to go!
Yeah.

12:08.729 --> 12:10.395
Man #2: Wait, wait, wait!
We're getting one more.

12:10.397 --> 12:11.896
I promise.

12:11.898 --> 12:13.198
Man:
Gotta move out, folks!

12:13.200 --> 12:14.700
When we find her,

12:14.701 --> 12:16.201
we're gonna take her to the same
hospital where you are.

12:16.203 --> 12:19.104
Critical on this rig.
Now means now, folks. Come on.

12:19.106 --> 12:21.406
No time out for sentiment.

12:21.408 --> 12:23.341
[ Radio chatter ]

12:31.451 --> 12:33.051
[ Siren wails in distance ]

12:47.400 --> 12:49.467
Gina: Five of haldol
and double his restraints.

12:49.469 --> 12:50.785
That guy gets out of his bed
again, glue him down.

12:50.786 --> 12:52.102
Excuse me, I have a pregnant
patient over there.

12:52.105 --> 12:53.972
Nobody's checking her in.

12:53.973 --> 12:55.840
Well, unless that baby's about
to fall out or take my job,

12:55.842 --> 12:57.208
she'll have to wait a minute.

12:57.210 --> 12:58.276
Carla?

12:59.880 --> 13:02.380
Friend of yours?
Sure is.

13:02.382 --> 13:03.548
Carla used to be
a resident here.

13:03.550 --> 13:06.117
So, what's going on?

13:06.119 --> 13:07.786
Passed out in a store.

13:07.788 --> 13:09.554
Some do-gooder
called 911.

13:09.556 --> 13:11.356
Oh, I hate the do-gooders.

13:11.358 --> 13:13.458
California's full of them.
That and Kale.

13:13.460 --> 13:16.528
Gina perello,
E.R. director.

13:16.530 --> 13:17.829
Carla niven.

13:17.831 --> 13:20.031
Malaya's old girlfriend Carla.

13:20.033 --> 13:21.966
Congrats on the baby.

13:21.968 --> 13:23.434
Bummer on the cancer.

13:23.436 --> 13:25.870
Thank you.

13:29.009 --> 13:30.542
I like her.

13:30.544 --> 13:32.443
Well, she's got her own style,
that's for sure.

13:32.445 --> 13:33.895
[ Chuckles ]

13:33.896 --> 13:35.346
So, what were you doing
when you passed out?

13:35.348 --> 13:37.515
I was buying an ice cream.

13:38.952 --> 13:40.318
I didn't even get to eat it.

13:41.054 --> 13:42.487
Will you do an ultrasound first?

13:42.489 --> 13:44.088
I want to make sure
the cargo's okay

13:44.090 --> 13:45.490
before you check out the plane.

13:45.492 --> 13:46.858
You got it.

13:46.860 --> 13:48.059
Come on.

13:49.529 --> 13:52.463
Woman: Help!

13:52.465 --> 13:55.233
[ Panting ]

13:55.235 --> 13:56.568
[ Woman coughing ]

13:58.972 --> 14:01.072
Help!

14:02.542 --> 14:04.609
Where the hell's Mario?

14:04.611 --> 14:06.531
I don't know, but this is
our last bag of saline.

14:08.181 --> 14:09.447
[ Banging ]

14:10.984 --> 14:13.551
Please!
I can't get out!

14:15.188 --> 14:18.056
I can't move!

14:18.058 --> 14:20.358
[ Sobbing ]

14:20.360 --> 14:22.327
My leg!

14:22.329 --> 14:23.595
It's broken!

14:23.597 --> 14:26.064
I don't have time to stabilize
the fracture.

14:26.066 --> 14:28.233
Just get me out of here!

14:28.235 --> 14:29.601
This is gonna hurt like hell.

14:29.603 --> 14:33.004
[ Screaming ]

14:34.341 --> 14:35.974
[ Rapid beeping ]

14:35.976 --> 14:37.575
That thing got a short or what?

14:37.577 --> 14:38.877
It keeps going off.

14:38.879 --> 14:40.612
No.

14:40.614 --> 14:43.615
I adjusted the levels a little,
that's all.

14:43.617 --> 14:47.185
I set it up so it can warn me
slightly ahead of any problems.

14:50.490 --> 14:54.359
Anxiety is totally normal
after a heart attack.

14:54.361 --> 14:56.561
I don't have anxiety.

14:56.563 --> 14:59.264
I'm just being careful,
that's all.

14:59.266 --> 15:01.666
Thing's gonna give<i> me</i>
a panic attack in a minute.

15:01.668 --> 15:04.068
It wasn't a panic attack.

15:04.070 --> 15:05.670
It was an aftershock.

15:05.672 --> 15:07.372
Oh.

15:07.373 --> 15:09.073
You mean like
after an earthquake?

15:11.978 --> 15:13.378
All right.

15:13.380 --> 15:16.614
I am gonna go flirt
with the nurses.

15:16.616 --> 15:20.652
I'm terrible at it,
so if you want to be my wing,

15:20.654 --> 15:22.387
you'll come hang, huh?

15:24.057 --> 15:25.556
How many times have you fallen?

15:25.558 --> 15:27.492
Uh, just a few.

15:27.494 --> 15:29.928
Five or six, maybe.

15:29.930 --> 15:31.596
Any nausea, vomiting?

15:31.598 --> 15:33.598
Yeah.
But, you know, that's...

15:33.600 --> 15:36.034
That's just morning sickness,
I'm sure.

15:36.036 --> 15:37.669
Yeah.

15:40.307 --> 15:43.374
Carla, look.
Mm.

15:45.478 --> 15:46.511
[ Chuckles ]

15:46.513 --> 15:47.712
Oh, my God.

15:53.386 --> 15:56.454
Excuse me.
I have a C.T. open for you.

15:56.456 --> 15:57.722
V.I.P. Treatment.

15:57.724 --> 16:00.625
Thank you.

16:01.962 --> 16:05.229
Kenny: [ Shivering ]
Doctor...

16:05.231 --> 16:06.664
I-I'm not gonna make it.

16:06.666 --> 16:08.399
I know I'm not gonna make it.

16:08.401 --> 16:09.734
I wa... I want the phone,
please.

16:09.736 --> 16:11.703
I want... I want to...
I want to talk to my family.

16:11.705 --> 16:13.071
I want to say goodbye to my...

16:13.073 --> 16:15.073
I want to say goodbye
to my daughters.

16:18.578 --> 16:20.144
[ Dialing ]

16:22.182 --> 16:24.282
[ Ringing ]

16:24.284 --> 16:25.984
Girls:<i> Hi!</i>

16:25.985 --> 16:27.685
[<i> Giggling</i> ]<i> You've reached</i>
<i>the wylar family!</i>

16:27.687 --> 16:29.654
<i>We can't come to the phone
right now...</i>

16:29.656 --> 16:31.689
<i>So leave a message
at the beeeep!</i>

16:31.691 --> 16:32.724
[ Beep ]

16:32.726 --> 16:34.692
Sw-sweetheart,
it's daddy again.

16:34.694 --> 16:36.761
I-I... I'm... I'm leaving you
another message.

16:36.763 --> 16:38.229
I-I, um...

16:38.231 --> 16:42.133
I...Want to say
that I love you.

16:42.135 --> 16:44.002
I love you very much.

16:44.004 --> 16:45.603
I love you with all my heart.

16:45.605 --> 16:48.573
I want you to live your life
knowing that you were loved.

16:48.575 --> 16:51.409
Just know that, okay?

16:51.411 --> 16:53.244
Damn it, Mario.

16:55.048 --> 16:56.647
Mario: Angus!
Oh, thank God.

16:56.649 --> 16:57.715
Heather!

16:58.752 --> 17:00.685
Whoo! [ Laughs ]

17:00.687 --> 17:02.253
I have never been happier
to see you.

17:02.255 --> 17:03.521
He'll call you back.
[ Beep ]

17:03.523 --> 17:05.289
This is all I could
get off the truck.

17:05.291 --> 17:06.591
What took you so long?

17:06.593 --> 17:09.027
Had to save a woman
from a burning car.

17:10.430 --> 17:12.130
That's right.
Deal with it.

17:13.533 --> 17:15.666
One, two, three.

17:15.668 --> 17:17.335
[ Car creaking, all grunting ]

17:17.337 --> 17:18.703
Almost, almost.
Come on.

17:18.705 --> 17:20.371
Two...
Kenny: I don't want
to die in here!

17:20.373 --> 17:21.172
Three!
I don't want to die in here!

17:21.174 --> 17:22.473
Aah!

17:23.676 --> 17:26.177
All right. Come on.
Aah. Aah!

17:26.179 --> 17:27.712
Dig!
Come on, everybody, dig!

17:27.714 --> 17:30.782
All right, everybody.
Dig, dig, dig.

17:30.784 --> 17:32.784
[ Grunting ]
[ Groans ]

17:32.786 --> 17:34.218
I feel a leg.

17:34.220 --> 17:36.621
Angus: Here, I got his hands.
All right.

17:36.623 --> 17:37.455
Two, three.

17:37.457 --> 17:38.790
Slow, slow. Easy.

17:41.227 --> 17:42.760
Slow. Easy. Hey.

17:42.762 --> 17:45.063
Nice and easy.
Nice and easy.

17:45.065 --> 17:47.498
Okay, we got you.
We got you. You're good.

17:47.500 --> 17:48.766
Okay. You're good.

17:48.768 --> 17:51.369
That's it.
Mario: You're good.

17:52.405 --> 17:55.406
Make sure not to move that.
I'll find you some water.

17:55.408 --> 17:56.774
Silver dodge
with a bumper sticker

17:56.776 --> 17:58.342
that said "my dog's not fat,
it's a husky."

17:58.344 --> 18:00.111
Have you seen
anything like it?
Mnh-mnh.

18:00.113 --> 18:02.213
Okay. Well, if you find it,
come back and get me, okay?

18:02.215 --> 18:03.514
I saw that car.

18:03.516 --> 18:05.149
There was a woman inside.
I black-tagged her.

18:05.151 --> 18:06.584
What were her injuries?

18:06.586 --> 18:09.153
Unconscious,
pulse was weak and thready,

18:09.155 --> 18:10.555
huge laceration to her left leg.

18:10.557 --> 18:12.390
Catastrophic blood loss.
Why the black tag?

18:12.392 --> 18:13.791
Because she isn't gonna make it.

18:13.793 --> 18:15.093
Dr. Rorish,
it was the right call.

18:15.095 --> 18:16.327
Malaya, where's the car?

18:16.329 --> 18:18.329
About 200 yards down
in the number-three Lane.

18:18.331 --> 18:19.331
But...

18:19.332 --> 18:20.331
Where do you think you're going?

18:20.333 --> 18:22.300
I'm going to check on a patient.

18:22.302 --> 18:23.835
You heard your resident.
She's a black tag.

18:23.837 --> 18:26.021
No offense to Dr. Pineda,

18:26.022 --> 18:28.206
but I can't rely on a first-year
resident's eval on this one.

18:28.208 --> 18:29.640
I promised the boy.

18:29.642 --> 18:31.509
Promises to little boys don't
hold water in the zone.

18:31.511 --> 18:33.277
Out here, we treat patients
under strict protocol.

18:33.279 --> 18:34.796
Put your bag down.
Now.

18:34.797 --> 18:36.314
I don't report to you.
Actually, you do.

18:36.316 --> 18:37.849
And if you disobey me out here,

18:37.851 --> 18:39.584
you're in violation of state
and federal law.

18:39.586 --> 18:42.153
I will have you arrested
right here, right now.

18:48.761 --> 18:51.729
Are we really gonna
let this... Guy

18:51.731 --> 18:54.215
tell us who to treat
and how to treat them?

18:54.216 --> 18:56.700
I can go check again.
Maybe I wasn't thorough enough.

18:56.703 --> 18:58.803
No, Malaya.
You stay here.

18:58.805 --> 19:00.485
[ Woman screaming,
man yells indistinctly ]

19:03.409 --> 19:06.410
All right, Malaya.
I got it.

19:06.412 --> 19:08.596
Hold down the fort.

19:08.597 --> 19:10.781
Miles: [ Speaks indistinctly ]
I need at least one more.

19:10.783 --> 19:11.849
Woman: Copy that.

19:17.357 --> 19:18.456
[ Phone rings ]

19:25.298 --> 19:26.430
[ Elevator bell dings ]

19:26.432 --> 19:28.833
Jesse.

19:28.835 --> 19:30.735
What are you doing here?

19:30.737 --> 19:32.737
Dr. Carla niven!

19:32.739 --> 19:35.573
Always glad to see you.
Just not glad to see you here.

19:35.575 --> 19:36.607
What's going on?

19:36.609 --> 19:38.276
[ Scoffs ]
I'm old news.

19:38.278 --> 19:39.310
What's up with you?

19:39.312 --> 19:42.180
Uh, I'm getting a 2-d echo.

19:42.182 --> 19:42.947
Heart attack.

19:42.949 --> 19:45.650
No way.
When'd that happen?

19:45.652 --> 19:47.485
A week ago, eight days.

19:47.486 --> 19:49.319
Eight days ago?
You have any complications?

19:49.322 --> 19:51.856
A few bloops and bleeps.

19:51.858 --> 19:53.457
No complications.

19:53.459 --> 19:55.660
Listen, you should be
discharged by now.

19:55.662 --> 19:57.929
Who's the idiot who ordered
the 2-d echo?

19:57.931 --> 20:00.898
You can't be too careful,
you know.

20:00.900 --> 20:04.302
Oh, so you're the idiot?
You ordered your own test?

20:04.304 --> 20:07.972
23% of people who have a first
heart attack have a second one.

20:07.974 --> 20:10.908
77% don't.

20:12.645 --> 20:14.812
I'd kill for those odds.

20:17.951 --> 20:19.350
[ Chuckles ]

20:19.352 --> 20:20.985
You know, you always used to say

20:20.987 --> 20:23.221
that the flip side
of everyone's best quality

20:23.223 --> 20:25.073
is their worst quality.

20:25.074 --> 20:27.114
You know what your best quality
is, don't you, mama?

20:27.927 --> 20:30.361
You care.

20:30.363 --> 20:33.231
What's my worst?

20:33.233 --> 20:35.299
You worry.

20:35.301 --> 20:38.769
There's only one prescription
for that. Get up.

20:38.771 --> 20:43.674
Jesse, didn't we already get
a 2-d echo on you last week?

20:44.644 --> 20:47.245
Let me guess...

20:47.247 --> 20:48.279
It was normal?

20:48.281 --> 20:49.680
No, don't listen to her.

20:49.682 --> 20:50.548
Don't you dare listen to him.

20:50.550 --> 20:52.283
Don't listen to him.

20:56.289 --> 20:57.722
Guess what?

20:58.791 --> 21:00.491
It's a boy.

21:01.928 --> 21:04.528
He's gonna be beautiful.

21:04.530 --> 21:07.398
And smart as hell,
just like his mommy.

21:07.400 --> 21:08.733
Take care.

21:08.735 --> 21:10.968
Thank you.

21:17.043 --> 21:21.312
Help! Help!
I need help!

21:21.314 --> 21:23.281
In here! In here!
My wife's in here!

21:23.283 --> 21:24.615
She's...

21:24.617 --> 21:26.417
She landed pretty hard.
I can't get her to move.

21:26.419 --> 21:28.569
Ma'am?
Y-you got to help her.

21:28.570 --> 21:30.720
Ma'am, can you hear me?
Okay, uh, get me some towels.

21:30.723 --> 21:31.889
Something, quick.
What is it?

21:31.891 --> 21:33.324
We got to roll her,
stabilize her.

21:33.326 --> 21:34.425
Nice and slow, okay?

21:34.427 --> 21:37.061
One, two, three.
That's it.

21:37.063 --> 21:38.663
Okay.
We need to apply pressure.

21:38.665 --> 21:41.399
Heather: Mario...
Popliteal pulses are weak.

21:41.401 --> 21:43.034
Uh, femoral pulse is...

21:43.036 --> 21:46.304
The hemorrhaging
is catastrophic.

21:46.306 --> 21:47.972
Okay, I know, okay,
she's lost a lot of blood.

21:47.974 --> 21:49.040
This is what we're gonna do.

21:49.042 --> 21:50.675
We're gonna focus in
on her head.

21:50.677 --> 21:52.443
The blood loss has already
caused too much damage.

21:52.445 --> 21:53.928
Look at her pupils.

21:53.929 --> 21:55.412
Man: Why aren't you
getting towels?

21:55.415 --> 21:56.815
What are you doing?
Get some towels.

21:56.816 --> 21:57.782
Why aren't you doing something?

21:57.784 --> 21:59.317
Man:
I need a doctor over here!

21:59.319 --> 22:00.668
I'm sorry.

22:00.669 --> 22:02.018
Your wife's injuries
are too serious.

22:02.021 --> 22:03.321
You said you were gonna
apply pressure.

22:03.322 --> 22:04.622
That's what you just
said, right?
I did.

22:04.624 --> 22:05.923
I was hoping we could apply
pressure, but...

22:05.925 --> 22:07.325
What, are you just gonna
leave her here to die?

22:07.327 --> 22:08.738
Sir, what's your name?

22:08.739 --> 22:10.150
No, I'm not talking to you.

22:10.151 --> 22:11.562
[ Crying ] Please,
you have to save my wife.

22:11.564 --> 22:13.431
Don't listen to her.
Her name is Lisa.

22:13.433 --> 22:16.067
She's a pre-school teacher,
and nothing ever gets her down.

22:16.069 --> 22:17.601
She's the bravest person
you will ever meet,

22:17.603 --> 22:19.103
and she's going
to get through this.

22:19.104 --> 22:20.604
Do you hear me? She's gonna
make it through this.

22:20.606 --> 22:21.639
Man #2:
I got a burn victim!

22:21.641 --> 22:23.374
Go.
Man: Please!

22:23.376 --> 22:24.942
If there was anything
we could do,

22:24.944 --> 22:26.877
okay, anything, we would.
I'm sorry.

22:26.879 --> 22:28.446
Please don't leave her!
Please, please.

22:28.448 --> 22:30.081
She's still breathing!

22:30.083 --> 22:33.684
She's everything I have
in this world! Please!

22:33.686 --> 22:36.454
If you knew how strong she was,
you wouldn't be doing this.

22:36.456 --> 22:38.889
Not if you knew!
Please!

22:39.992 --> 22:41.525
Heather:
Mario, get out here!

22:41.527 --> 22:43.794
I'm sorry.

22:43.796 --> 22:44.862
[ Man cries ]

22:44.864 --> 22:47.365
Neil:
This is it, leanne.

22:47.367 --> 22:49.967
All right. Connie?
Hey, Connie, Connie.

22:49.969 --> 22:51.669
Can you hear me?

22:51.670 --> 22:53.370
Thigh laceration.
Significant bleed down here.

22:53.373 --> 22:54.805
Okay.

22:54.807 --> 22:56.707
She's still got a pulse.

22:56.709 --> 22:58.976
Barely.

22:58.978 --> 23:00.978
You thinking what I'm thinking?

23:02.115 --> 23:04.115
That Malaya made the right call?

23:04.117 --> 23:05.516
Did she?

23:05.518 --> 23:07.017
No!

23:07.019 --> 23:10.154
Okay, Connie.

23:10.156 --> 23:12.123
We found your son.

23:12.125 --> 23:14.892
He's gonna be all right.

23:14.894 --> 23:17.995
[ Stapling ]
Okay? You hear me?

23:17.997 --> 23:20.097
All he wanted was
to take care of you.

23:20.099 --> 23:24.001
So we're gonna get you back
to him, okay?

23:24.003 --> 23:26.036
Leanne, look. This leg wound
goes all the way down.

23:26.038 --> 23:29.173
I am not gonna tell another kid
that his mother's dead.

23:31.110 --> 23:32.676
Her foot is completely crushed
in this metal.

23:32.678 --> 23:33.844
There's no way
we're getting it out.

23:33.846 --> 23:35.179
We can still get<i> her</i> out.

23:35.181 --> 23:37.548
[ Siren wails ]

23:37.550 --> 23:39.016
I'll find a saw.

23:57.870 --> 23:59.603
Hello?!

23:59.605 --> 24:02.506
Can you hear me?

24:02.508 --> 24:06.977
I'm a doctor!
Can anybody down there hear me?!

24:06.979 --> 24:09.113
Girl: Yes! I hear you!
I hear you!

24:09.115 --> 24:10.915
Please, you have to help us!

24:10.917 --> 24:12.583
Is your name Lily?

24:12.585 --> 24:13.984
Yes!
Yes, it's me, Lily!

24:13.986 --> 24:16.270
Please help us!

24:16.271 --> 24:18.555
My mom and my brother
are badly hurt!

24:18.558 --> 24:20.224
[ Branch snaps ]
Aah!

24:20.226 --> 24:21.492
[ Grunting ]

24:32.905 --> 24:34.105
Lily:
[ Echoing ] Are you okay?

24:34.106 --> 24:36.006
Do you need help?
[ Groans ]

24:36.008 --> 24:37.208
[ Normal voice ]
Are you hurt?

24:37.210 --> 24:38.542
[ Groaning ]

24:42.482 --> 24:45.783
Hi, Lily.
I'm Dr. Lorenson.

24:45.785 --> 24:47.551
Mom!
Mom, she's a doctor!

24:47.553 --> 24:50.588
Come quick.
My mom and my brother are hurt.

24:50.590 --> 24:52.156
Okay.

24:53.926 --> 24:55.559
What's wrong?

24:55.561 --> 24:57.228
I dislocated my shoulder.

24:57.230 --> 25:00.030
I'm okay. I'm okay.

25:00.032 --> 25:01.966
I'm gonna need your help,
though, okay?

25:01.968 --> 25:04.134
Can you grab that bag
over there for me?

25:05.938 --> 25:07.738
Ooh!

25:11.911 --> 25:13.711
Are you really a doctor?

25:13.713 --> 25:15.579
Yes, I am.

25:15.581 --> 25:18.282
But I'm counting on my assistant
here to help me.

25:18.284 --> 25:20.951
[ Strained ] Lily tried climbing
out, but it's too steep.

25:20.953 --> 25:22.553
And we tried honking the horn,
but it's...

25:22.555 --> 25:23.521
What's your name?
Broken.

25:23.523 --> 25:24.889
Katherine.

25:24.891 --> 25:26.257
She hurt her neck,
and she can't move her legs.

25:26.259 --> 25:30.294
Go check my son, please.
I'm okay. Help her.

25:32.698 --> 25:34.598
[ Moans ]

25:34.600 --> 25:37.568
Okay. Katherine...

25:37.570 --> 25:39.103
Listen to me carefully.

25:39.105 --> 25:42.172
You fractured your neck when you
were thrown from the car.

25:42.174 --> 25:45.242
The paralysis you're feeling
right now may not be permanent,

25:45.244 --> 25:47.611
but it's crucial that you don't
move your head one inch.

25:47.613 --> 25:49.580
Lily, I need you
to grab me something

25:49.582 --> 25:50.948
to support your mom's head
on either side

25:50.950 --> 25:52.583
so she can't move it.
Can you do that?

25:52.585 --> 25:53.851
Okay.

25:55.655 --> 25:57.588
You have a pretty serious
head laceration

25:57.590 --> 25:59.189
I'm gonna need to stitch up.

25:59.191 --> 26:00.558
You've lost a lot of blood.

26:00.560 --> 26:02.326
Check on my son.
Please.

26:02.328 --> 26:03.328
His name is Elliot.

26:03.329 --> 26:05.796
Okay. Lie still.

26:08.301 --> 26:09.900
Hi, Elliot.

26:09.902 --> 26:11.969
My name is Christa.

26:11.971 --> 26:13.904
You're having trouble breathing?

26:13.906 --> 26:17.074
[ Straining ] A little.
My throat hurts.

26:17.076 --> 26:20.744
I tried to get up,
but my hips hurt too much.

26:20.746 --> 26:22.346
Can you say "aah"?

26:22.348 --> 26:23.847
Aah...
Ah.

26:27.053 --> 26:30.254
Feel this popping sensation
as I'm pressing onto your skin?

26:30.256 --> 26:32.056
Yeah, it's, uh, crackly.

26:32.058 --> 26:34.758
Okay.
It's called crepitus.

26:34.760 --> 26:38.028
It's air from your windpipe
leaking into your skin.

26:38.030 --> 26:39.964
It means you fractured
your trachea.

26:39.966 --> 26:43.734
I need you to breathe slowly
and try not to talk.

26:43.736 --> 26:45.302
[ Gasps lightly ]

26:45.304 --> 26:47.304
You've been very brave,

26:47.305 --> 26:49.345
but I need you to try and rest
your voice now, okay?

26:51.310 --> 26:53.210
I assume you don't have a phone?

26:53.212 --> 26:55.779
There's no reception.
I tried until the battery died.

26:58.784 --> 27:00.651
[ Groans ]

27:03.623 --> 27:04.855
[ Monitor beeping ]

27:07.693 --> 27:09.360
Just say it.

27:10.997 --> 27:13.731
It's in my brain, isn't it?

27:13.733 --> 27:17.034
It's a tumor.

27:17.036 --> 27:18.969
Secondary to the leukemia.

27:18.971 --> 27:22.840
The swelling around it is
pressing on your brain stem.

27:22.842 --> 27:26.744
Unfortunately, this is
an aggressive type of tumor.

27:26.746 --> 27:28.145
I'm afraid it won't be long

27:28.147 --> 27:30.748
before it stops
your breathing...

27:30.750 --> 27:32.316
And then your heart.

27:32.318 --> 27:35.052
Carla...

27:35.054 --> 27:38.122
I need to be blunt here.

27:38.124 --> 27:40.357
If you die with that baby
inside of you, there's...

27:40.359 --> 27:41.425
What?

27:41.427 --> 27:43.027
Well, obviously we need to call

27:43.029 --> 27:44.328
o.B. In and induce...

27:44.330 --> 27:45.829
No, I'm not dying tonight.

27:45.831 --> 27:47.431
That's... that's ri...

27:47.433 --> 27:49.833
That's ridiculous.
I'm not dying tonight.

27:49.835 --> 27:52.703
I have plenty of time left.

27:52.705 --> 27:53.837
A-at least let me get you
an o.B. Consult.

27:53.839 --> 27:54.839
Please.

27:54.840 --> 27:56.774
Fine. Fine.

28:01.213 --> 28:04.882
But I'm not delivering
this baby at 30 weeks.

28:06.886 --> 28:09.286
Okay? And you're not
telling Malaya.

28:09.288 --> 28:11.155
She can help you
through this, Carla.

28:11.157 --> 28:13.323
She's made it perfectly clear
that she can't handle it,

28:13.325 --> 28:14.692
or she doesn't want to.

28:14.694 --> 28:16.260
Okay. Okay.

28:16.262 --> 28:18.328
But can you do me a favor?
Hmm?

28:21.033 --> 28:22.833
Think about it.

28:26.872 --> 28:28.872
Man:
Shortness of breath.

28:28.874 --> 28:30.808
Triage, right now.

28:30.810 --> 28:32.376
We intact?

28:32.378 --> 28:34.244
Something's wrong.
It hurts.

28:34.246 --> 28:35.713
Set it right over here.

28:35.715 --> 28:37.114
Dr. Pineda, where the hell
is Dr. Rorish?

28:37.116 --> 28:38.048
I don't know.

28:38.050 --> 28:39.249
Do you have a phone?

28:39.251 --> 28:40.851
I have to call
my sister... Back.

28:40.853 --> 28:42.219
What you need to do
is stop talking.

28:42.221 --> 28:43.721
Pulse ox is 90%.

28:43.723 --> 28:46.190
Let's get an oxygen mask on her
right away.

28:46.192 --> 28:47.858
Take slow, deep breaths.

28:47.860 --> 28:48.892
She doesn't know where I am.

28:48.894 --> 28:49.727
87%.

28:49.729 --> 28:51.195
I think she has a pneumo.

28:51.197 --> 28:52.162
We're gonna have to get
a chest tube in her right away.

28:52.164 --> 28:53.480
Do you know how to do that?

28:53.481 --> 28:54.797
There's probably shards
and fragments

28:54.800 --> 28:55.983
of broken bone in there,

28:55.984 --> 28:57.167
so it's not gonna be
an easy chest tube at all.

28:57.169 --> 28:58.368
I think I can do it.

28:58.370 --> 28:59.737
Out here, "I think I can"
is good enough.

28:59.739 --> 29:00.739
Do it.

29:01.874 --> 29:04.074
Okay, Amy, what do we got?

29:04.075 --> 29:06.275
8-year-old Jason riner.
B.P. 110 over 64.

29:06.278 --> 29:07.745
Heart rate 112.

29:07.747 --> 29:09.096
Sat'ing high 80s.

29:09.097 --> 29:10.446
Nauseous.
Vomited three times en route.

29:10.449 --> 29:12.850
A doctor said
they'd bring my mom here.

29:12.852 --> 29:14.284
Jason, I'm Dr. Guthrie.

29:14.286 --> 29:17.454
I need you to lie still so that
we can make you all better.

29:17.456 --> 29:19.156
Seat-belt sign
to the abdomen.

29:19.158 --> 29:20.758
Possible internal bleeding.

29:20.760 --> 29:22.793
My seat belt caused me to bleed?

29:22.795 --> 29:24.762
Your seat belt
saved your life, son.

29:24.764 --> 29:26.797
[ Squirting ]

29:26.799 --> 29:27.998
Man: You got it.

29:28.000 --> 29:30.467
Good lung slide here.

29:30.469 --> 29:33.837
Probable lung contusion,
but no pneumo.

29:33.839 --> 29:36.507
Jason, we're gonna take you
on a ride upstairs

29:36.509 --> 29:38.242
so we can take some pictures
of your tummy, okay?

29:38.244 --> 29:40.410
What if my mom comes in?
She won't know where I am.

29:40.412 --> 29:42.946
When your mom gets here,
I'll come and find you.

29:42.948 --> 29:43.814
What's your mom's name?

29:43.816 --> 29:45.449
Connie riner.

29:45.451 --> 29:48.152
[ Siren wails ]

29:48.154 --> 29:49.052
You ready?

29:49.054 --> 29:50.921
As I'll ever be.

29:50.923 --> 29:52.763
Soon as you do this,
we run her back to triage!

29:54.426 --> 29:56.326
Good?
Yeah.

30:00.199 --> 30:01.298
[ Grunting ]

30:02.868 --> 30:05.002
Christa: Okay. Remember how
I showed you last time.

30:05.004 --> 30:07.404
It's just like tying a shoe.

30:07.406 --> 30:08.338
Through this loop, right?

30:08.340 --> 30:09.873
Right.

30:09.875 --> 30:12.442
Cut when I say.

30:12.444 --> 30:13.343
Ready?

30:13.345 --> 30:14.845
Ready.

30:14.847 --> 30:17.014
And...

30:17.983 --> 30:19.917
now!

30:21.987 --> 30:22.886
Got it.

30:22.888 --> 30:24.438
[ Elliot gasping ]

30:24.439 --> 30:25.989
Elliot?
Lily, what's going on?

30:25.991 --> 30:27.574
Katherine, don't move.

30:27.575 --> 30:29.158
Something's wrong.
Christa: Elliot?

30:29.161 --> 30:31.195
Calm down. Calm down.
Deep breaths.

30:31.197 --> 30:33.030
I know you're scared.
[ Gasping ]

30:33.032 --> 30:34.698
Is he breathing?!

30:34.699 --> 30:36.365
Elliot, I need to look down
your throat again, okay?

30:36.368 --> 30:38.685
It's okay.
It's okay.

30:38.686 --> 30:41.003
Try and relax your throat
and jaw as best you can.

30:41.006 --> 30:41.839
Is he gonna be okay?

30:41.841 --> 30:42.906
Lily, go to your car

30:42.908 --> 30:44.508
and see if you can
find me a pen.

30:44.510 --> 30:46.143
A pen?
Yes, an ink one. Hurry!

30:46.145 --> 30:47.211
Are you gonna write something?

30:47.213 --> 30:48.345
No.

30:48.346 --> 30:49.478
I'm gonna try and keep
your brother breathing.

30:49.481 --> 30:50.981
[ Gasping ]

30:50.983 --> 30:53.383
[ Breathing raggedly ]

30:53.385 --> 30:55.953
[ Indistinct conversations,
radio chatter ]

30:55.955 --> 30:58.522
God, where are you guys?

30:58.524 --> 31:00.924
Hey, Terrence,
I need that ultrasound.

31:00.926 --> 31:02.559
Her anatomy shifted
from the crash.

31:02.561 --> 31:03.894
I can't find my markers.

31:03.896 --> 31:05.329
It's in use.
Five minutes.

31:05.331 --> 31:07.231
She can't wait five minutes!

31:07.233 --> 31:08.966
[ Siren wails ]

31:08.968 --> 31:10.934
Woman: 18 Gauge!

31:10.936 --> 31:12.302
Okay.
There should be some there!

31:12.304 --> 31:13.971
Best guess, then.

31:14.907 --> 31:16.640
I'm sorry, Jocelyn.

31:16.642 --> 31:17.941
[ Monitor beeps rapidly ]

31:17.943 --> 31:19.643
Enough already.

31:19.645 --> 31:21.912
[ Beeping stops ]

31:21.914 --> 31:23.146
[ Sighs ]

31:23.148 --> 31:26.016
[ Beeping resumes ]

31:26.018 --> 31:28.051
[ Groans ]

31:28.053 --> 31:31.321
[ Monitor flatlines ]

31:33.192 --> 31:35.359
Jack?

31:35.361 --> 31:37.895
Jack, you with me, bro?

31:37.897 --> 31:40.530
I need help!
Anybody!

31:40.532 --> 31:43.033
[ Floor buffer whirring ]
I've got a guy coding in here!

31:43.035 --> 31:45.969
[ Panting ]

31:50.009 --> 31:51.642
[ Device beeping ]

31:54.513 --> 31:56.113
Okay.

32:00.686 --> 32:03.020
My wife, she's awake!

32:03.022 --> 32:04.321
What?
She's awake!

32:04.323 --> 32:05.956
I tried to tell you,
she's strong.

32:05.958 --> 32:06.924
For God's sake, hurry.
Please.
I'll be right back.

32:06.926 --> 32:08.458
Please.

32:08.460 --> 32:10.060
[ Indistinct shouting ]

32:10.062 --> 32:11.295
He's turning blue.

32:11.297 --> 32:12.963
Katherine: Oh, God!

32:12.965 --> 32:15.332
What's happening?
Please don't let him die!

32:15.334 --> 32:16.967
[ Crying ] Please
don't let my baby die!

32:16.969 --> 32:19.202
No one's gonna die.

32:19.204 --> 32:21.305
No one's gonna die.

32:21.307 --> 32:24.408
I'm gonna make a small hole
in his windpipe...

32:24.410 --> 32:25.609
In his neck, here...

32:25.611 --> 32:27.711
So that we can pass a tube
through it

32:27.713 --> 32:29.863
that he can breathe through.

32:29.864 --> 32:32.014
Thing is, I'm gonna need both
hands in order to do it.

32:32.017 --> 32:33.483
So I need you to help me

32:33.485 --> 32:35.485
push my shoulder back
into its socket.

32:35.487 --> 32:37.587
I can't do that.
Yes, you can.

32:37.589 --> 32:40.457
But we need to move fast.
Don't think about it.

32:40.459 --> 32:43.126
[ Groans ]

32:43.128 --> 32:45.462
Okay.
Take my wrist.

32:45.464 --> 32:48.098
Put your foot under my arm.

32:48.100 --> 32:49.666
[ Groans ]

32:49.668 --> 32:51.368
Oof.

32:51.370 --> 32:53.036
Okay.

32:53.038 --> 32:55.505
[ Breathless ] I want you to
pull back as hard as you can,

32:55.507 --> 32:57.274
like you're opening a door
that's stuck.

32:57.276 --> 32:58.742
Ready?

32:58.744 --> 33:00.043
Okay.

33:00.045 --> 33:01.645
[ Groaning ]
Sorry.

33:01.647 --> 33:02.679
Pull harder.

33:02.681 --> 33:04.281
[ Screaming ]

33:09.455 --> 33:11.989
[ Monitor flatlining ]

33:11.991 --> 33:14.524
I need help, por favor!

33:14.526 --> 33:16.526
[ Device beeps rapidly ]
I need juice. Juice.

33:22.501 --> 33:24.101
Charge.

33:24.102 --> 33:25.702
[ Defibrillator charging ]
Okay, here we go.

33:25.704 --> 33:28.472
Idios mío!

33:28.474 --> 33:30.674
[ Electricity zaps ]

33:31.777 --> 33:34.478
What the hell?
I thought this was v-tach.

33:34.480 --> 33:36.780
[ Sighs ] It was.

33:36.782 --> 33:39.449
You got him back
to sinus rhythm?

33:39.451 --> 33:41.385
But you're a patient.

33:41.387 --> 33:43.620
I'm a nurse, bro.

33:43.622 --> 33:46.656
Always a nurse.

33:46.658 --> 33:48.625
Woman: Bring those two
over this way.

33:48.627 --> 33:50.527
[ Siren wailing ]
Man: Here you go.

33:53.332 --> 33:54.631
Where the hell have<i> you</i> been?

33:54.633 --> 33:56.533
Doing our jobs.
Angus, get over here.

33:56.535 --> 33:57.501
P.E.A. Due to blood loss.

33:57.503 --> 33:58.668
Open a central line.

33:58.670 --> 34:00.070
Push whatever we've got.
She needs fluids.

34:00.072 --> 34:01.505
She's seizing.
Ativan now, please.

34:01.507 --> 34:03.473
There are consequences
to your arrogance, doctors.

34:03.475 --> 34:04.475
So arrest us.

34:04.476 --> 34:06.209
That's not what I mean.

34:06.211 --> 34:07.444
<i>This</i> is the consequence
of your decision.

34:07.446 --> 34:09.246
Pushing ativan now.

34:10.582 --> 34:12.449
It's working.
This one's getting
on that ambulance!

34:12.451 --> 34:14.518
Yeah, this one too!
Pulse is thready,
but it's back.

34:14.520 --> 34:17.387
You overstepped, and you
countermanded a direct order.

34:17.389 --> 34:19.089
Yeah, maybe I did,
but I made a medical decision.

34:19.091 --> 34:21.425
You made an emotional decision.
You see this woman here?

34:21.427 --> 34:22.960
Yellow tag when she arrived.

34:22.961 --> 34:24.494
I wasn't available
to help your resident

34:24.496 --> 34:25.946
with a blind chest tube,

34:25.947 --> 34:27.397
and now it took longer
than it should have.

34:27.399 --> 34:29.599
She was deprived of oxygen.
She might have brain damage.

34:29.601 --> 34:31.168
That was my fault.
I couldn't get that tube in.

34:31.170 --> 34:32.702
It is not your fault.
It's ours.

34:32.704 --> 34:34.538
He's right, leanne.
Our math doesn't work.

34:34.540 --> 34:36.040
We may have saved Connie,

34:36.041 --> 34:37.541
but we did it at the expense
of someone else.

34:37.543 --> 34:39.543
If that woman doesn't make it,
it's on us.

34:39.545 --> 34:41.411
Man: [ Shouts indistinctly ]
Ready to go!

34:41.413 --> 34:44.114
Hey, guys, I need to get
on the ambulance now! Come on.

34:44.116 --> 34:45.482
Let's go, let's go, let's go!

34:45.484 --> 34:46.750
Okay.
Sorry to interrupt here,

34:46.752 --> 34:48.251
but, uh, nobody's heard
from Christa.

34:48.253 --> 34:50.353
What do you mean?
Well, no one's seen her,

34:50.355 --> 34:51.721
she hasn't checked in,
she hasn't answered her radio.

34:51.723 --> 34:53.423
You should go back
with Connie.
All right. Will do.

34:53.425 --> 34:55.125
I'll go and look for Christa.

34:55.127 --> 34:56.359
Angus, take over.

34:56.361 --> 34:57.727
Okay. Lily, next up,

34:57.729 --> 35:00.197
I need you to bite off
both ends of the pen.

35:00.199 --> 35:02.199
Like this?

35:02.201 --> 35:05.569
Okay. And the other side,
so it's open like a straw.

35:05.571 --> 35:07.404
Got it.

35:07.406 --> 35:08.605
We've got to do this now.

35:08.607 --> 35:10.674
[ Wheezing ]

35:11.810 --> 35:13.577
Have you done this before?

35:13.579 --> 35:15.178
Doesn't happen very often.

35:15.180 --> 35:18.215
There's gonna be
a little blood, okay?

35:19.284 --> 35:20.817
Okay.

35:27.693 --> 35:29.459
[ Moans softly ]

35:29.461 --> 35:30.894
Damn!
That's a lot of blood.

35:34.133 --> 35:37.767
Come on, come on, come on,
come on, come on, come on.

35:40.205 --> 35:41.205
Lily, hand me the pen.

35:41.206 --> 35:43.406
[ Wheezing ]

35:45.677 --> 35:47.177
[ Blows ]

35:47.178 --> 35:48.678
I see it, I see it!
His chest is moving!

35:48.680 --> 35:50.714
Okay. Hand me the bag.
Let's tape it up.

35:54.286 --> 35:57.154
Okay.
You take over.

35:57.156 --> 35:58.655
Squeeze the bag
every 10 seconds.

35:58.657 --> 36:00.223
Not too hard.

36:07.232 --> 36:09.232
[ Sighs ]

36:09.234 --> 36:11.835
You did fantastic, Lily.

36:11.837 --> 36:13.470
His breath is okay.

36:13.472 --> 36:17.674
Your brother is lucky to have
such a brave sister.

36:29.621 --> 36:31.354
How are my kids?

36:31.356 --> 36:34.424
He's stable,
and breathing on his own.

36:34.426 --> 36:35.959
Lily was a great assistant.

36:35.961 --> 36:38.595
She is fearless.

36:38.597 --> 36:39.729
How are you feeling?

36:39.731 --> 36:40.797
A little cold.

36:48.207 --> 36:50.774
Nobody knows we're down here,
do they?

36:50.776 --> 36:53.243
What if nobody comes?

36:57.916 --> 36:59.583
Risa, is triage open?

36:59.585 --> 37:00.283
Yes, Dr. Rorish.

37:00.285 --> 37:01.551
Get the gurney.

37:01.553 --> 37:02.986
Uh, right inside.

37:02.988 --> 37:06.756
[ Chatter ]

37:06.758 --> 37:08.141
We're being overrun.

37:08.142 --> 37:09.525
You're all being called back
here now.

37:09.528 --> 37:11.328
Look, I haven't heard
from Christa yet,

37:11.330 --> 37:12.896
and now I'm missing Mario
and Heather.

37:12.898 --> 37:14.664
I'm not leaving without
all of our team.

37:14.666 --> 37:17.234
You are<i> not</i> search and rescue.
You are a doctor.

37:17.236 --> 37:18.301
Get back here.

37:18.303 --> 37:19.269
[ Cellphone beeps ]

37:19.271 --> 37:20.770
[ Sighs ]

37:20.772 --> 37:21.972
[ Phone slams ]

37:21.974 --> 37:24.341
Risa, call upstairs and get me
some doctors

37:24.343 --> 37:25.408
and nurses down here.

37:25.410 --> 37:26.710
Risa:
Who am I calling?

37:26.711 --> 37:28.011
I don't care if you call
dermatology.

37:28.013 --> 37:28.979
We need some help.

37:28.981 --> 37:31.314
Help has arrived.

37:31.316 --> 37:32.949
I could kiss you
right now, Jesse!

37:32.951 --> 37:34.784
My heart couldn't take it.

37:34.786 --> 37:35.786
[ Laughs ]

37:35.787 --> 37:37.654
Hey, Jason, listen to me.

37:37.656 --> 37:40.824
We had to put a tube in her
mouth to help her breathe,

37:40.826 --> 37:44.594
so she won't be able to talk.

37:44.596 --> 37:48.765
In truth, she won't be able
to respond at all.

37:48.767 --> 37:51.034
Is she dead?

37:51.036 --> 37:52.969
No. She's alive.

